@node Importing Models
@subsection Importing Models

When a component refers to other components or interfaces and their
details, the declaration of these has to be known.

An import clause is available to load the declaration from separate
files holding interface or component declarations.

@subsubsection Syntax

    The keyword @b{import} is used to import interface or component
    definition files.

@example
import ModelName.dzn;
@end example

Each import clause will look on the file system for a file with the required
name, and include the content.

For the time being the file should be located in the same directory as
the current model.  So 'import Console.dzn' expects a file
'./Console.dzn'

@subsubsection Examples

@subsubsection A component importing an interface

The component Leaf implements the ISensor interface for which the
declaration is imported using the import statement.

@example
import ISensor.dzn
component Leaf
@{
  provides ISensor sensor;
    behaviour
    @{
        on sensor.event(): @{ @}
    @}
@}
@end example

