@node Binding Ports
@subsection Binding Ports

A component can be decomposed into a group of components.  A grouping of
components is called a @b{@i{system}}.

Component instances in the composition are connected by binding their
ports.  Only ports with an equal interface definition and opposite
direction can be bound together.

@subsubsection Syntax

A binding statement takes the form of

@example
component1_instance_name.port <=> component2_instance_name.port
@end example
Only ports with an equal interface definition and opposite direction can be bound together.

@subsubsection Examples

@subsubsection Decomposition into components and binding their ports.

Here a component is decomposed into two other components C1 and C2.

@example
interface I1
@{
  in void event();
@}
component C1
@{
  provides I1 i1;
@}
component C2
@{
  requires I1 i1;
@}
component Decomposition
@{
  system
  @{
    C1 c1;
    C2 c2;
    c1.i1 <=> c2.i1;
  @}
@}
@end example

