@node Execution Semantics
@chapter Execution Semantics

The execution semantics of Dezyne are illustrated using different model
examples and the corresponding sequence diagrams.

When interpreting the models and corresponding sequence diagrams, keep
in mind that the body of an event is executed atomically in the context
of its behaviour.

For an in-event all action statements are executed depth-first.  All
out-events are stored in event queues at the receiving components.  After
the completion of all action statements, just before control is passed
back to the caller, a component will flush its own queue of pending out
events.  Recursively all out-events are handled this way.

