@end table

@node Glossary
@chapter Glossary

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .15 .5 .2
@headitem Term @tab Context @tab Definition @tab Chapter
@item Action
@tab Concept
@tab Statement as part of the response to a trigger event.
@tab -
@item behaviour
@tab Keyword
@tab Start of the behaviour section within an interface or component definition; this keyword must be followed by @{@}.
@tab @xref{Interface and Component Behaviour}

@item Bind
@tab Concept
@tab To associate two ports within a system section using the Dezyne language's &lt;=&gt; operator.
@tab -

@item blocking
@tab Keyword
@tab Qualifier to indicate that the executing of the trigger is blocked till a corresponding reply is given on the port of the trigger
@tab @xref{Blocking}

@item bool
@tab Keyword
@tab Boolean type identifier.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item Compliance
@tab Concept
@tab Whether or not, the behaviour of a component complies to the behaviour specification of the interface of each provided port.
@tab -

@item Component
@tab Concept
@tab Unit of definition and instantiation.  A component has zero or more ports.  A component has a behaviour section, system section, or none.
@tab -

@item component
@tab Keyword
@tab Begins the definition of a component; this keyword must be followed by an identifier and @{@}.
@tab @xref{Component Models}

@item condition
@tab Concept
@tab If-then-else statement.
@tab -

@item else
@tab Keyword
@tab Else part of condition statement.
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item enum
@tab Keyword
@tab Enumeration type declaration.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item Event
@tab Concept
@tab An event is declared as part of an interface and represents the type of the messages communicated between components.  An event is implemented as a
 function call.
@tab -

@item extern
@tab Keyword
@tab Type definition which can be used for data variables and data parameters.  Followed by an identifier and $$'s.  The part between $$'s is used in the
 generated code as the type definition for these data variables and
 parameters.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item external
@tab Keyword
@tab Qualifier of a provided port definition indicating that the out events can be possibly delayed which is taken into account during verification.
@tab @xref{External}

@item false
@tab Keyword
@tab Boolean value false.
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item Guard
@tab Concept
@tab A boolean expression between [ ] as prefix of a statement
@tab -

@item Hand-written
@tab Concept
@tab A hand-written component is defined as a component without a behaviour or system section in the component definition.  The implementation should be
 provided in the target source language.
@tab -

@item if
@tab Keyword
@tab The &quot;if&quot; keyword is followed by a boolean expression and a statement and optionally the keyword &quot;else&quot; followed by a second
 statement
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item illegal
@tab Keyword
@tab illegal statement.  As a direct response indicates that the given event in the given state is not allowed to be communicated.  Within a component, the illegal statement is also allowed within a function or if-then-else statement, indicating that the illegal statement should never be executed, i.e.  comparable with &quot;assert(FALSE);&quot; of the C-language.
@tab @xref{Using illegal}

@item import
@tab Keyword
@tab The file following the import keyword is loaded and expanded at the location of the import statement
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item in
@tab Keyword
@tab Indicates for an event of an interface that the event is an incoming event '''or''' indicates for a data parameter of an event or function that the value of the parameter is incoming
@tab @xref{Specifying Events}

@item inevitable
@tab Keyword
@tab A trigger event that will inevitably occur provided no other events occur.
@tab @xref{Using inevitable and optional}

@item injected
@tab Keyword
@tab Qualifier of a required port to indicate that the binding of the port occurs at a higher level in the system hierarchy.
@tab @xref{Component Models}

@item inout
@tab Keyword
@tab Indicates for a data parameter of an event or function that the value of the parameter is incoming at the begin of the event or function call, and
 outgoing at the end.
@tab -

@item Interface
@tab Concept
@tab An interface defines a set of events and the underlying protocol how components communicate between each other via their ports.
@tab -

@item interface
@tab Keyword
@tab Begins the definition of an interface; this keyword must be followed by an identifier and @{@}.
@tab @xref{Interface Models}

@item namespace
@tab Keyword
@tab -
@tab @xref{Namespaces}

@item on
@tab Keyword
@tab Identifies an on-event statement which for one or more trigger events defines the corresponding response.
@tab @xref{Actions}

@item optional
@tab Keyword
@tab A trigger that optionally can happen.
@tab @xref{Using inevitable and optional}

@item otherwise
@tab Keyword
@tab Defines a catch-all guard which is true only if all the other guard expressions in a list of guarded statements evaluate to false.
@tab @xref{Specifying Stateful Behaviour}

@item out
@tab Keyword
@tab Indicates for an event of an interface that the event is an outgoing event '''or''' indicates for a data parameter of an event of function that the value of the parameter is outgoing
@tab @xref{Specifying Events}

@item Port
@tab Concept
@tab Within a component definition, a named instance of an interface.
@tab -

@item provides
@tab Keyword
@tab Used in a component to define a port and its type which the component will provide.
@tab @xref{Ports}

@item reply
@tab Keyword
@tab Statement that defines the value that will be returned as result of the triggering event.
@tab @xref{Reply}

@item requires
@tab Keyword
@tab Used in a component to define a port and its type which the component will use.
@tab @xref{Ports}

@item return
@tab Keyword
@tab return statement; specifies the return value of a function (if any) and exits the function.
@tab @xref{Using functions}

@item Sequence view
@tab Window
@tab Message sequence chart (result of simulation or verification).
@tab -

@item State
@tab Concept
@tab A state consists of all values of the state variables in scope.
@tab -

@item subint
@tab Keyword
@tab A type representing a finite sequence of integers, expressed as @{m..n@} where m and n are integers and m &lt;= n, for example @{-2..1@}.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item System
@tab Concept
@tab A component containing a system section.
@tab -

@item system
@tab Keyword
@tab Starts the system section of a component.  A system section consists of two parts: instantiations of subcomponents, followed by all the bindings
 among the sub-components and ports of the component.
@tab @xref{Decomposing a Component}

@item Trace
@tab Concept
@tab An execution trace is a sequence of events representing a possible execution scenario.
@tab -

@item true
@tab Keyword
@tab Boolean value true.
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item Type
@tab Concept
@tab An enum, subint, bool, or extern.
@tab -

@item Variable
@tab Concept
@tab Declared within a behaviour section.  A variable can be either a state variable which can be used a part of a guard of condition or a data variable
 which can be used as a parameter of events or functions
@tab -

@item Verification
@tab Concept
@tab The execution of the verification
 engine which verifies for interfaces and components whether they are free of livelock, deadlock, and illegal behaviour.  Also, for a component it is
 verified whether a component adheres to all the protocols (behaviour) of the interfaces of the ports of the component.  During verification, all possible
 execution scenarios are considered guaranteeing a 100% coverage.
@tab -
@end multitable

